Management of HIV-seropositive newborn infants. Personal experience apropos of 179 cases. A follow-up study of 179 cases of human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) seropositive neonates born from HIV seropositive mothers is reported. At the time of the present study, HIV infection resulting from maternofetal transmission was found in 50 cases, while 108 infants were not infected HIV infection remained uncertain in 16 cases